- Laura, you're on scut.
- I was on scut yesterday.

57
00:02:48,952 --> 00:02:52,571
Oh, and just for that, you're
on scut tomorrow. Get lost!

58
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:55,306
Dr. Karev, this is
Dr. Norman Shales.

59
00:02:55,409 --> 00:02:58,543
- Hey.
- Strong handshake. That's a good sign.

60
00:02:58,645 --> 00:03:00,378
Norman's transferring
in from UCLA.

61
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,180
I want him to work with you.

62
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:05,484
- Are you the new ob/gyn guy?
- I don't have a specialty yet.

63
00:03:05,586 --> 00:03:06,969
Norman is an intern.

64
00:03:08,422 --> 00:03:11,456
- You'll be his resident.
- He's my intern?

65
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:14,676
Don't you worry. This tugboat's
ready to pull his own weight.

66
00:03:14,778 --> 00:03:18,330
- Age is just a number, right?
- Absolutely.

67
00:03:18,432 --> 00:03:20,115
A pretty important number.

68
00:03:22,185 --> 00:03:23,705
- Hey.
- Hey.

69
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:26,638
- You OK?
- I don't know.

70
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,091
I think it's all just
hitting me, you know.

71
00:03:29,193 --> 00:03:30,809
Stupid Burke, dumping me.

72
00:03:30,911 --> 00:03:36,681
Then stupid Mama coming
to reclaim her magic necklace.

73
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:43,154
- You want to talk about it?
- No. Not really. Not yet.

74
00:03:43,256 --> 00:03:45,035
If there's anything I can do...

75
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:48,126
You know, I just wish I
had a good bloody surgery.

76
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:51,329
You know, bloody surgeries
make me feel better.

77
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,968
One, Two, Three,
Four. Follow me.

78
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:04,258
Joanne, this is why you and I
need to get sick. These doctors.

79
00:04:04,361 --> 00:04:06,422
One's more handsome
than the next.

80
00:04:06,446 --> 00:04:09,297
And here comes the
handsomest one of them all.

81
00:04:09,399 --> 00:04:11,416
- Hi, Dr. Webber.
- Connie.

82
00:04:11,518 --> 00:04:13,329
He took my appendix
out three years ago.

83
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:16,171
Barely left a scar. How's Adele?

84
00:04:16,273 --> 00:04:21,126
Um... She's good.
Good. Marriage is hard.

85
00:04:21,228 --> 00:04:26,364
But we're dating again... and
she agreed to date me tonight.

86
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:29,450
But... more importantly,
how are you doing?

87
00:04:29,552 --> 00:04:32,304
I just had a little bump on
my tongue removed, is all.

88
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:34,889
Couple of taste buds.
It was a touch of cancer,

89
00:04:34,991 --> 00:04:37,069
so I'm here to
have the rest out.

90
00:04:37,093 --> 00:04:41,096
I mean, you know, the
cancer. Not the taste buds.

91
00:04:41,198 --> 00:04:42,875
I don't know
exactly how bad it is

92
00:04:42,899 --> 00:04:45,139
because Dr. Sloan's been quiet.

93
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:48,169
Because you don't let him
get a word in edgewise, is why.

94
00:04:48,272 --> 00:04:49,704
Uh, how is she, Dr. Sloan?

95
00:04:49,806 --> 00:04:52,507
We just got back the
pathology report, Connie.

96
00:04:52,609 --> 00:04:56,494
Unfortunately, the cancer is a bit
more widespread than we'd hoped.

97
00:04:56,596 --> 00:04:58,947
It's over 60 percent
of your tongue.

98
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,833
Well, what does she do? Chemo?

99
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:06,204
I think the best bet is a
microvascular free flap.

100
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,605
Dr. Grey?

101
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:10,091
He'll remove the
cancerous part of the tongue

102
00:05:10,193 --> 00:05:12,827
and then reconstruct it with
a strip of flesh from your legs.

103
00:05:12,929 --> 00:05:15,964
- George?
- Uh, the extra flesh would

104
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:17,777
provide the bulk
your tongue needs

105
00:05:17,801 --> 00:05:19,561
to breathe properly,
chew, swallow.

106
00:05:19,636 --> 00:05:21,669
And talk?

107
00:05:27,694 --> 00:05:30,595
Dr. Sloan? I'll be
able to talk, won't I?

108
00:05:30,698 --> 00:05:33,915
You will be able
to talk, Connie.

109
00:05:34,017 --> 00:05:37,201
I just don't know how
well you'll be understood.

110
00:05:40,607 --> 00:05:42,473
- It'll be OK.
- It'll be OK.

111
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:45,126
<i>Nurse Hollister, Peds ICU.</i>

112
00:05:45,228 --> 00:05:46,762
What are you doing in my clinic?

113
00:05:46,864 --> 00:05:48,680
I thought you didn't
work in the clinic.

114
00:05:48,782 --> 00:05:52,950
I don't. But I thought I'd get my new
intern, Norman, settled in with you.

115
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,098
Bailey's the best.
You'll really learn.

116
00:05:55,122 --> 00:05:56,404
Oh. Pleased to meet you.

117
00:05:56,506 --> 00:06:00,108
You want to leave Norman with
me while you troll for surgeries.

118
00:06:04,331 --> 00:06:07,048
The dude's got a bum hip and
he smells like arthritis cream.

119
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:08,378
He can't keep up.

120
00:06:08,402 --> 00:06:10,935
Come on. Do me a favor
and I'll do you a favor.

121
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:14,205
I'm calling in my favor
now. Curtain Five.

122
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:17,676
You can take your intern and
show him how we do an H & P.

123
00:06:17,778 --> 00:06:21,563
- Nice to meet you, Norman.
- Thank you.

124
00:06:21,665 --> 00:06:25,033
Hunter, I'm Dr. Karev.
This is Dr. Shales.

125
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:27,768
- What's going on?
- My son is on drugs.

126
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:31,005
- I'm not on drugs, Mom.
- I wasn't born yesterday.

127
00:06:31,107 --> 00:06:33,608
I know the signs.
He's lethargic, irritable,

128
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:35,771
school work's gone
down the drain.

129
00:06:35,795 --> 00:06:39,314
- I'm not on drugs.
- There are a host of reasons

130
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,766
why your son could be
exhibiting those symptoms.

131
00:06:41,868 --> 00:06:43,628
I think we should
run some tests.

132
00:06:43,704 --> 00:06:46,037
But first a drug
test, Dr. Shales?

133
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:49,074
- I'm right to want a drug test?
- Yeah, I just said that.

134
00:06:49,176 --> 00:06:51,242
Mrs. Chapman, you are not wrong.

135
00:06:51,344 --> 00:06:54,128
My Mary Beth, God rest
her soul, was just like you.

136
00:06:54,231 --> 00:06:56,264
When one of our kids
started heading down

137
00:06:56,366 --> 00:06:59,317
that slippery slope,
she just knew it.

138
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:03,671
You have a mother's
instinct. Right, Dr. Karev?

139
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,708
Yeah. Right.

140
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:13,731
OK. What happened?
George. It's Really Old Guy.

141
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,945
We could bring a
marching band in here.

142
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:19,404
- What happened with Callie?
- What happened?

143
00:07:20,290 --> 00:07:22,218
You were gonna
tell her last night.

144
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:25,776
I tried, but she would not
let me. She wouldn't let me.

145
00:07:25,878 --> 00:07:28,596
And I wanted to kill her,
but then I couldn't kill her

146
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,932
because she did help
me through a lot of stuff,

147
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:32,767
and it was a lot of stuff.

148
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:36,571
Then I wanted to kill her again
because who marries someone

149
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:39,457
who just buried their father?
And then I went to bed.

150
00:07:39,559 --> 00:07:41,292
So what does this mean?

151
00:07:42,863 --> 00:07:45,008
I told you I needed a
minute before rounds.

152
00:07:45,032 --> 00:07:47,415
- We heard you saved
a guy yesterday.
- What?

153
00:07:47,534 --> 00:07:49,484
- Rounds!
- Excuse me.

154
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,548
We'll start in here.

155
00:07:52,572 --> 00:07:55,623
Graziella, what can you
tell us about Really Old Guy?

156
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,675
- He has a name.
- I know he has a name.

157
00:07:57,777 --> 00:07:59,622
We call him Really Old Guy.

158
00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:02,096
Eighty-two year old
semi-comatose male.

159
00:08:02,198 --> 00:08:05,750
Came in a year ago status
post fall and is post-op day 352...

160
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:08,086
Which means he hasn't
woken up for a year.

161
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:10,271
So what's the treatment plan?

162
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:13,091
Um... um...

163
00:08:14,211 --> 00:08:15,660
It's really very simple.

164
00:08:15,762 --> 00:08:18,179
Daily labs and dialysis
three times a week.

165
00:08:18,281 --> 00:08:21,899
Don't bother with
any more dialysis.

166
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:26,587
I plan to die today, so
it won't be necessary.

167
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,277
Nice to meet you.

168
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:35,663
And while I think Really
Old Guy is charming

169
00:08:35,782 --> 00:08:41,169
in a neglected patient kind
of way, my name is Charlie.

170
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:43,654
Charlie Yost.

171
00:08:55,652 --> 00:08:57,919
Hey, I just heard. Welcome back.

172
00:08:58,021 --> 00:08:59,782
Is it true? Really
Old Guy woke up?

173
00:08:59,806 --> 00:09:00,922
He has a name.

174
00:09:01,024 --> 00:09:04,225
This time tomorrow you
can call me Really Dead Guy.

175
00:09:04,327 --> 00:09:06,410
I don't think Mr. Yost
knows who you are.

176
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:08,680
Sure I do. That's Meredith.

177
00:09:08,782 --> 00:09:12,383
She and the brain doctor are
always running hot and cold.

178
00:09:12,485 --> 00:09:14,485
And you're Alex.

179
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:17,805
You still got a thing for
that old patient of yours?

180
00:09:17,907 --> 00:09:22,160
I was semi-comatose, Blondie.
I could still hear you guys.

181
00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:25,263
Get a CT, a CBC and chemistries.

182
00:09:25,365 --> 00:09:26,665
Your kidneys may be working,

183
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:29,167
which may be why you
woke up. It's good news.

184
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:32,003
Oh, it just means now I
got two things to do today.

185
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:35,740
- Take a pee and die.
- Nobody's dying. "Aah."

186
00:09:37,193 --> 00:09:39,310
- Functional muscle transfer.
- What?

187
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:41,947
For Connie. I was reading
up on glossectomies

188
00:09:42,049 --> 00:09:42,964
and saw the procedure.

189
00:09:43,066 --> 00:09:44,861
We could microsurgically

190
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:47,046
reinnervate her
hypoglossal nerve.

191
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:50,054
A nerve graft? It's too risky.

192
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:52,257
The free flap's
still your best bet.

193
00:09:52,359 --> 00:09:55,655
Even if that goes well, you and I
know she'll never speak the same.

194
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:59,280
- That woman loves to talk.
- What's a functional
muscle transfer?

195
00:09:59,382 --> 00:10:02,384
You won't find it in the
books. It's cutting edge.

196
00:10:02,486 --> 00:10:05,520
Connect the nerves from the leg
with the nerves from the tongue.

197
00:10:05,622 --> 00:10:08,490
- Gives her a shot
at really speaking.
- If it works.

198
00:10:08,591 --> 00:10:10,592
They've only done a
half a dozen of them.

199
00:10:10,694 --> 00:10:13,794
Better than none. Sometimes
you got to push the envelope.

200
00:10:13,896 --> 00:10:16,681
Better to do a surgery that
neither of you have done

201
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:19,634
than do a surgery that you
know at least gives her a chance

202
00:10:19,736 --> 00:10:23,504
to have a normal life? Do
you know how to do this?

203
00:10:26,643 --> 00:10:30,711
Are you saying that we're too
old to learn new ways, O'Malley?

204
00:10:30,813 --> 00:10:32,093
No.

205
00:10:32,148 --> 00:10:34,493
Saying we're old dogs,
can't learn new tricks?

206
00:10:34,517 --> 00:10:37,068
- No. I was just asking...
- We're not old dogs.

207
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:39,304
- We still got it.
- OK.

208
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:43,624
I did do a functional
muscle transfer

209
00:10:43,727 --> 00:10:45,209
to restore elbow function once.

210
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:48,212
Elbow, tongue. That's pretty
close. Come on. What do you say?

211
00:10:48,298 --> 00:10:50,798
- Let's light this candle.
- Yes, sir.

212
00:10:53,186 --> 00:10:55,620
- Age is just a number.
- Yes, sir.

213
00:10:58,558 --> 00:10:59,907
Excuse me.

214
00:11:01,762 --> 00:11:03,845
I got Karev down
in the clinic all day.

215
00:11:03,947 --> 00:11:06,281
- I hope that's not a problem.
- Nope.

216
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,750
I know how you like
to be told these things,

217
00:11:08,851 --> 00:11:11,219
- so I'm telling you.
- Thank you.

218
00:11:11,321 --> 00:11:14,071
You know, he tried to dump
a new intern on me, Karev.

219
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:15,523
Not interested in teaching.

220
00:11:15,625 --> 00:11:18,459
Thank you for letting me know.

221
00:11:30,006 --> 00:11:33,825
- You ever feel old?
- I'm young. I'm a fetus.

222
00:11:33,926 --> 00:11:36,227
You ever feel like
there's going to be a time

223
00:11:36,329 --> 00:11:37,995
when new techniques pass you by?

224
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:40,915
- I'm a genius and a scholar.
- Shut up.

225
00:11:42,085 --> 00:11:45,353
Meredith isn't telling
Cristina about us.

226
00:11:46,389 --> 00:11:49,056
And, well, she tells
Cristina everything.

227
00:11:49,158 --> 00:11:51,692
- I thought you broke that off.
- I meant to.

228
00:11:52,912 --> 00:11:55,479
You think she's gonna
want to get back together.

229
00:11:55,581 --> 00:11:56,658
No.

230
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,182
You think she's going to grow up

231
00:11:58,285 --> 00:12:01,286
and get all whole and
want a relationship.

232
00:12:01,370 --> 00:12:04,572
- I do not.
- You're a bad liar.

